{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"All direct and transitive dependencies are extracted from the manifest and included in the vulnerability check.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is between manifest parsing, dependency graph resolution (including transitives), and the scanner handoff. A unit test of only one parser function can miss dropped transitive nodes at module boundaries.","test_description":"Run scanner dependency collection against fixture projects (`package.json` + lockfile, `requirements.txt` + resolved tree) and assert the final set sent to the vuln-check stage contains all expected direct and transitive packages with versions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The vulnerability database query returns results that match the exact version ranges in the manifest, not just the package name.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The key risk is query-construction and response-matching across modules (range parsing -> API request builder -> result filter). This can fail even if each unit appears correct in isolation.","test_description":"Wire the real range parser + query builder + response matcher against a local stub vuln API that returns different CVEs for adjacent ranges; assert only CVEs matching the manifest’s exact range are reported.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.17,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The severity sorting places Critical above High above Medium above Low, with CVEs of the same severity sorted by CVSS score.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is deterministic ordering logic inside one sorting function/comparator; no external boundary is required to expose the real failure.","test_description":"Provide an unsorted in-memory CVE list covering all severities and tied severities with varying CVSS; assert output order is `Critical > High > Medium > Low`, and within each severity CVSS is descending.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The manifest modification changes only the affected dependency's version, leaving all other entries unchanged.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failures usually occur at parser/editor/writer boundaries (e.g., wrong path update, collateral edits), not in a single pure function.","test_description":"Run the manifest update pipeline on real fixture files containing multiple dependencies and formatting quirks; diff before/after and assert exactly one dependency version changed and all other keys/values remain identical.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The auto-generated pull request is created on the real repository with the correct single-dependency diff.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This behavior explicitly depends on real git/GitHub API interactions and repository state. Mocking can hide auth, branch, permission, and diff-creation failures.","test_description":"Against a real test repository, run PR creation end-to-end: create branch, commit manifest change, open PR, then verify on the remote PR that the diff contains only the targeted dependency version bump.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.9,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"A major version bump is correctly identified as a breaking change based on semver comparison.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Semver major-bump detection is local deterministic logic; one function can be validated with table-driven cases.","test_description":"Table-test version pairs (including prerelease/build metadata cases) and assert `breaking=true` only when the target major version is greater than current major per semver rules.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.92,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When a breaking change is detected, PR creation is skipped and a review flag is surfaced in the scanner output.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is orchestration logic across semver decisioning, PR service invocation gate, and reporting output. Unit-testing one component can miss miswired control flow.","test_description":"Execute scanner flow with a fixture that triggers a breaking bump; assert PR service is not invoked and scanner output includes the required review flag/reason in the produced report artifact.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
